{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_136","type":"agent_message","text":"Implemented the websocket client skeleton end to end and checkpointed it in commit `0dfb491` (`feat(prompt-29): frontend websocket client skeleton`). The frontend now has a typed realtime contract/parser, a reconnecting session-scoped websocket client, runtime-store event reduction that merges live stage/chat/progress updates into the current session snapshot, and a visible live-status card in the workspace header. The main wiring lives in [sessionRealtimeClient.ts](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/frontend/src/features/session/live/sessionRealtimeClient.ts), [sessionRuntimeStore.ts](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/frontend/src/features/session/sessionRuntimeStore.ts), and [SessionWorkspacePage.tsx](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/frontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.tsx).\n\nVerification passed with `npm run lint`, `npm test` (`11` files, `36` tests), `npm run build`, and `npm run format:check`. Browser QA was also completed with mocked API responses inside the running compose `browser` container because the local compose backend currently exits on an existing `secrets.yaml` validation issue unrelated to this prompt. Screenshots are at [prompt-29-session-workspace-desktop.png](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/.artifacts/webapp-qa/prompt-29-session-workspace-desktop.png) and [prompt-29-session-workspace-mobile.png](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/.artifacts/webapp-qa/prompt-29-session-workspace-mobile.png). The required reviewer summary was written last to [29-frontend-websocket-client-skeleton.summary.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/prompts/29-frontend-websocket-client-skeleton.summary.md)."}}
